content.description: Begin sit starting on two crimps that are located in the horizontal seam, and reach up to a left hand crimp and right hand crimp.  Trend right, following the seam, using left incuts and right sidepulls. The stand start from the left and right crimps is V2.
content.location: This is located on the south face and ends on the southeast corner. It is also located to the left of the step in rocks along the ground.  Sit start on two crimps in the horizontal seam.

content.description: Sit start with a left hand on the obvious sidepull and right hand on the sloper.  Make a move straight up to the crimps and then out left to slopers.  Move up to the pinch and sloper, where the line transitions to a slab.
content.location: This is located on the SW corner of the boulder. The start is located to the west of the small ledge in the face, near the ground.  Sit start with a left sidepull and right sloper.
